HEADWORD: Bonze
<hw>Bon"ze</hw> <pr>(b⟦ocr⟧n"z⟦esl⟧; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>bonzo</ets>, fr. Japan. <ets>b⟦omac⟧zu</ets> a Buddhist priest: cf.
F. <ets>bonze</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Buddhist or Fohist priest, monk, or
nun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name was given by the Portuguese to the priests of
Japan, and has since been applied to the priests of China, Cochin China,
and the neighboring countries.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bonzer</ent>⟦br⟧
